# Unit Tests for Complex Services
#
# Rule: Unit tests must focus STRICTLY on complex business logic, calculations, state machines,
# or sophisticated data transformations within Services.
#
# Simple CRUD or direct Eloquent model/repository operations do not need individual Unit tests;
# they should be covered via API Feature Tests (end-to-end integration).
#
# Example Guidelines:
# 1. Mock external dependencies (Repositories, External APIs, Mailers) using Mockery or Laravel's built-in Mocks.
# 2. Test edge cases, boundaries, and intricate conditional branches within the service logic.
# 3. Ensure tests execute extremely fast by avoiding direct database/network hits unless absolutely necessary.
